{{One source|date=June 2011}} {{Infobox language |name=Lop |nativename=''Ľor télé / Льор теълеъ'' |states=[[China]] |region=[[Xinjiang]] Uyghur Autonomous Region |speakers=25,000 |date=no date |ref=<ref name=e12>{{Ethnologue12|uig|Uighur}}</ref><!--not in e11--> |familycolor=Altaic |fam1=[[Turkic languages|Turkic]] |fam2=[[Common Turkic languages|Common Turkic]] |fam3=[[Karluk languages|Karluk]] |fam4=[[Uyghur language|Uyghur]] |isoexception=dialect |glotto=lopn1238 |glottoname=Lopnor |glotto2=lopp1238 |glottoname2=Lop – duplicate entry |glottorefname2=Lop }}
'''Lop''', also known as '''Lopnor''' or '''Lopnur''' is a language{{Citation needed|date=April 2015}} spoken in [[Xinjiang]], [[China]].
==Classification== Lop belongs to the Karluk branch of Turkic languages, along with [[Uyghur language|Uyghur]] and [[Uzbek language|Uzbek]]. Its status as a distinct language from Uyghur is disputed. Although it has some features that differentiate it from [[Standard language|standard]] Uyghur, it is considered by some linguists to be one of its [[dialect]]s.{{Citation needed|date=April 2015}}
