'''Universal Allocation Per Child''' ({{lang-es|Asignación universal por hijo}}) is a [[social security]] program in Argentina. It pays a monthly subsidy to families for each child under 18 or disabled. Despite the name, it is not yet a universal program, and currently applies only to families who do not have a regular reported income. A plan is in place to enlarge the scope of the program.<ref>http://www.laarena.com.ar/la_ciudad-ampliaron-cobertura-1079615-115.html</ref><ref>http://www.eldiariodecarlospaz.com/sociedad/2016/3/19/macri-anuncio-ampliacion-asignacion-universal-hijo-23153.html</ref>

It was established in 2009 by a [[Necessity and Urgency Decree]], signed by president [[Cristina Fernández de Kirchner]].

